title: Welle sparks KU to men’s golf win
text:
October 26, 2015 
Advertisement 
El Paso, Texas  Kansas University senior Ben Welle played bogey-free golf Sunday to surge to a second-place finish at the Price’s Give ’Em Five Invitational, and the KU men’s golf team won its second team title of the season. 
Welle shot a career-best 8-under 64 to finish at 202 (14-under), five strokes behind winner Antoine Rozner of UMKC. 
“It was a great win today,” KU coach Jamie Bermel said. “I’m really proud of all of them but especially the seniors in particular.” 
Kansas won the team crown with 38-under 826, four strokes off the school record. 
Runner-up St. Mary’s shot 837. 
KU’s other scores: Chase Hanna, sixth, 207; Charlie Hillier, tied for eighth, 209; Connor Peck, tied for 20th, 212; Jacques Wilson, tied for 46th, 218; and Daniel Hudson, tied for 60th, 222. 
Butterfield Trail Golf Club
